Dashboards
Dashboards provide customizable visualizations for monitoring and controlling your system. Create piping and instrumentation diagrams (P&ID), custom monitoring interfaces, and control panels tailored to test operations.

Dashboard Navigation Panel
The Dashboard Navigation Panel (left side) displays all dashboards in the system, sorted alphabetically. Switch between dashboards by clicking their names. Use the search bar at the top to filter dashboards by name.

Dashboards with unpublished changes are indicated with a blue dot Unpublished changes indicator next to the dashboard name.

Click the Collapse Sidebar button Collapse Sidebar button to show or hide the navigation panel.

Creating and Editing Dashboards
To create a new dashboard, click the New Diagram button button at the top of the dashboard list. Then enter a dashboard name in the box above the new dashboard.

To edit an existing dashboard, click the Edit Dashboard button button in the top right corner to open edit mode.

Publishing Dashboards
When you create or edit a dashboard, it initially exists only on your device, as indicated by the On This Device label in the navigation panel. This allows you to create custom dashboards and iterate quickly without affecting other users.

Local Storage Warning

Dashboards stored on the local device use browser local storage and will be lost if browser data is cleared or if switching browsers or computers. Publish or download important dashboards to preserve them.

Publishing a dashboard automatically updates it for all connected Consoles. Publishing requires Commander privileges.

Dashboard Components
When editing a dashboard, the Dashboard Component Palette appears on the left.

Components fall into two categories:

Static components provide visual structure for diagrams but do not connect to telemetry (e.g., Check Valve, Relief Valve, Text labels, Heat Exchanger symbols)
Telemetry components display live data and enable control for telemetry channels (e.g., Telemetry Readout, Trace Plot, Boolean Switch, Tank)
Drag and drop components onto the canvas, then click them to configure properties such as linked channels, labels, colors, and sizes.

Multi Component Placement
To place multiple instances of a component in a grid arrangement, click the component in the palette to display a grid selector. Hover over the grid to highlight the desired number of rows and columns, then click and drag the arranged group onto the canvas.

