Custom Colors
Some dashboard components support custom colors for visual differentiation in P&ID diagrams. Custom colors help operators quickly identify related channels, distinguish subsystems, or match site-specific color conventions.

Color Use in Safety-Critical Displays

Human-machine interface (HMI) best practices recommend reserving high-saturation warm colors exclusively for alarms, warnings, and abnormal conditions. When reds, oranges, and yellows are used for general-purpose styling, genuine alerts lose their visual urgency and operators may miss safety-critical information.

The custom color palette intentionally excludes red, orange, and yellow. These colors are reserved for system status indicators.

Supported Components
Component	Effect
Boolean	Fill color when the value is true
Indicator	Border and text color
Switch	Border and text color for each switch state
Tank	Tank fill color
Telemetry Readout	Border and sparkline color
To set a custom color, click a component in edit mode to open its property panel and select a color from the picker. To clear a custom color, click the selected swatch again.

Status Override Behavior
Custom colors apply only when the channel is in the live state. Status colors take precedence when a channel is stale, pending, in error, or uninitialized, ensuring operators can always identify abnormal conditions regardless of custom styling.

Importing and Exporting Dashboards
Dashboards can be exported as JSON files for backup, version control, or sharing between systems. To access the dashboard JSON click the top right dashboard menu Menu and select View JSON from the menu, then paste the JSON and save or save and publish the dashboard.

Each dashboard JSON contains the component list, properties, and layout information needed to recreate the dashboard.

Image Handling

Images are not included in the JSON and must be re-uploaded when importing a dashboard.

